WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:17.016
2701!
Get the fuck out!

2
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.559
Is there
a MedicAlert bracelet?

3
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:21.061
- Did you get an ID on him?
- Student ID.

4
00:00:21.062 --> 00:00:22.980
- Name says Jackson Davis.
- That's a start.

5
00:00:22.981 --> 00:00:25.441
- Jackson. what's going on?
- Title 18!

6
00:00:25.442 --> 00:00:27.026
- Title section 508!
- Javadi. you're with us.

7
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:28.819
We're gonna take good care
of you. Mr. Davis.

8
00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:30.279
- You're in a safe place.
- You're okay.

9
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.447
- Get off!
- Trauma One.

10
00:00:31.448 --> 00:00:33.073
- Reasonableness! 2709!
- Okay. okay. Jackson.

11
00:00:33.074 --> 00:00:34.074
We're gonna need you
to calm down

12
00:00:34.075 --> 00:00:35.784
to get the Taser barbs
out of your neck.

13
00:00:35.785 --> 00:00:37.536
- Do you need to jump on that?
- Mm-mm.

14
00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:39.872
Covering calls for Dana.

15
00:00:39.873 --> 00:00:41.623
Stop talking to me.

16
00:00:41.624 --> 00:00:43.625
You can't! Title 2710--

17
00:00:43.626 --> 00:00:45.294
Hard to assess pupils.

18
00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:47.004
- Hard to assess anything.
- Yeah. yeah.

19
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.255
Wait till after he's sedated.

20
00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:49.798
- 10 of olanzapine.
- No. no.

21
00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:51.258
That'll take 15 minutes
to kick in.

22
00:00:51.259 --> 00:00:53.510
Uh. 5 of droperidol
puts him down in 5.

23
00:00:53.511 --> 00:00:55.345
No. you can't give it
without knowing his QT.

24
00:00:55.346 --> 00:00:58.098
Two beats of a rhythm strip
before he took off the leads.

25
00:00:58.099 --> 00:00:59.516
No.

26
00:00:59.517 --> 00:01:01.060
You can't be in here.
Get out!

27
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:02.770
That looks good.
Go with the droperidol.

28
00:01:02.771 --> 00:01:04.897
Get the fuck out!
Get off me!

29
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:06.732
Do we take
the Taser barbs out?

30
00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:08.233
- 2701.
- No.

31
00:01:08.234 --> 00:01:09.818
We got to wait
till he calms down first.

32
00:01:09.819 --> 00:01:12.529
Get off me. man.
2901. get out!

33
00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.448
Get out!
2710.

34
00:01:14.449 --> 00:01:16.992
Title 18. section--
1938.

35
00:01:16.993 --> 00:01:20.454
Mr. Randall.
happy 20th anniversary

36
00:01:20.455 --> 00:01:22.581
and a very happy
Fourth of July.

37
00:01:22.582 --> 00:01:24.416
But no sex fireworks
for you tonight.

38
00:01:24.417 --> 00:01:25.709
Give everything
a chance to heal.

39
00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:27.377
Don't worry. I will.

40
00:01:27.378 --> 00:01:29.379
Thanks. Doc.
Ow.

41
00:01:29.380 --> 00:01:31.340
We're going right back
through here. okay. ma'am?

42
00:01:31.341 --> 00:01:32.633
Oh. thank you.

43
00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:34.218
Change the dressing
twice a day.

44
00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:37.179
Doggy bag of the ointment
and nonstick gauze.

45
00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:38.680
Cool.
I know the drill.

46
00:01:38.681 --> 00:01:40.432
Come back if it starts
to ache or stink.

47
00:01:40.433 --> 00:01:42.518
Exactly.
Good luck. Stay safe.

48
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:44.186
Oh. shit. it's Daddy.
with your daddy.

49
00:01:44.187 --> 00:01:46.897
Lord. what'd
they get up to now?

50
00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:48.482
Treatin' and streetin'.

51
00:01:48.483 --> 00:01:50.734
"Pros from Dover."

52
00:01:50.735 --> 00:01:52.194
I'm sorry. Ms. Graham.

53
00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:54.488
I just saw the ASL note
in your chart.

54
00:01:54.489 --> 00:01:56.073
This is Lindsey.

55
00:01:56.074 --> 00:01:59.535
We'll bring you back
as soon as possible.

56
00:01:59.536 --> 00:02:00.703
Stay with her.

57
00:02:02.163 --> 00:02:04.749
All right.
Who here needs help?

58
00:02:06.876 --> 00:02:08.377
You?
You need help?

59
00:02:08.378 --> 00:02:11.171
Oh. no. no. no. ma'am.
I've been on these since 1987.

60
00:02:11.172 --> 00:02:13.549
This one here.
he got dizzy. fell down.

61
00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:15.801
Forgot
my blood-pressure medication.

62
00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:18.555
I left it back home in Georgia.

63
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.682
And presto.

64
00:02:21.683 --> 00:02:24.434
We're back. Mr. Digby.
with some IV antibiotics.

65
00:02:24.435 --> 00:02:28.105
First we scrub your outsides.
then we clean your insides.

66
00:02:28.106 --> 00:02:30.023
What do you need to document
in his chart?

67
00:02:30.024 --> 00:02:32.192
Uh. time started.
time completed.

68
00:02:32.193 --> 00:02:33.652
and any adverse reactions.

69
00:02:33.653 --> 00:02:36.280
What else?

70
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:39.825
Um. lot number
on the antibiotic vial.

71
00:02:39.826 --> 00:02:41.577
Excellent.
Mr. Digby.

72
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:43.203
It's just Digby.

73
00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:45.874
Digby. why'd you wait
so long to come see us?

74
00:02:47.458 --> 00:02:49.835
I don't like
going to doctors.

75
00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:51.211
Well. that makes two of us.

76
00:02:51.212 --> 00:02:52.921
We all need help
from time to time.

77
00:02:52.922 --> 00:02:55.757
Think maybe we could arrange
for some ongoing care?

78
00:02:55.758 --> 00:02:58.677
I just kind of want
to get patched up. you know?

79
00:02:58.678 --> 00:03:00.387
I do know.

80
00:03:00.388 --> 00:03:03.765
But that's today.
What's tomorrow?

81
00:03:03.766 --> 00:03:05.851
Sunday.

82
00:03:05.852 --> 00:03:08.770
Use the system.
That's what it's there for.

83
00:03:08.771 --> 00:03:11.315
Buddy of mine. Dylan.
knows all the angles.

84
00:03:11.316 --> 00:03:13.650
He even works
the occasional miracle.

85
00:03:13.651 --> 00:03:16.112
You think maybe
I could have him stop by?

86
00:03:18.114 --> 00:03:19.698
I guess. yeah.

87
00:03:19.699 --> 00:03:20.782
Great.

88
00:03:20.783 --> 00:03:22.868
- How about a sandwich?
- Yeah.

89
00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:24.704
Yes. please.

90
00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:28.749
<i>We always offer.</i>

91
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:31.501
Two most important things--
that they know we're here

92
00:03:31.502 --> 00:03:33.921
and that we'll never
stop offering.

93
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.297
Thanks for covering.
Princess.

94
00:03:35.298 --> 00:03:36.757
Anytime.

95
00:03:36.758 --> 00:03:38.592
Yo. can I get
some help over here?

96
00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:40.302
Yeah.
What's going on. man?

97
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:42.095
The crazy kid in there. screaming.

98
00:03:42.096 --> 00:03:44.056
- All right. have a seat.
- Yeah. that's him.

99
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.682
Still going nuts.

100
00:03:45.683 --> 00:03:48.018
Probably meth--
fucking animal.

101
00:03:48.019 --> 00:03:50.020
- What's your name. sir?
- You don't understand!

102
00:03:50.021 --> 00:03:52.231
Tony Chinchiolo.
campus security.

103
00:03:52.232 --> 00:03:53.899
Yeah. I was at work
when this happened.

104
00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:56.068
so I'm gonna need
everything documented.

105
00:03:56.069 --> 00:03:57.402
Okay.

106
00:03:57.403 --> 00:04:00.072
All right.
Heart rate's 89.

107
00:04:00.073 --> 00:04:01.823
Pulse ox 97.

108
00:04:01.824 --> 00:04:03.325
Scalp lac's tiny--

109
00:04:03.326 --> 00:04:04.326
- 5 millimeters.
- Ow.

110
00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:06.078
Should hold together
with Dermabond.

111
00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:08.080
Kid threw
a fucking chair at me.

112
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.998
Work-related injury
gets a full exam.

113
00:04:09.999 --> 00:04:12.125
- Jesse here will take you.
- Oh. no.

114
00:04:12.126 --> 00:04:13.627
I-I'm gonna stay here
till the cops come

115
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:16.421
so I can give my statement
and so I can watch him.

116
00:04:16.422 --> 00:04:17.923
Yeah.

117
00:04:17.924 --> 00:04:21.051
Trust me. you do not want
him getting out of there.

118
00:04:21.052 --> 00:04:23.679
Ow. fuck.

119
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:27.307
- Did she say anything?
- No more than she said to you.

120
00:04:27.308 --> 00:04:29.685
Nothing going on at home.
Nothing at school.

121
00:04:29.686 --> 00:04:32.354
- And you believe her?
- There's some flags.

122
00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:34.564
Bruising in various stages
of healing.

123
00:04:34.565 --> 00:04:35.899
She's a little withdrawn.

124
00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:37.901
doesn't engage much
for girls her age.

125
00:04:37.902 --> 00:04:40.237
But she could just be
a little shy...

126
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.863
or scared of being in here.

127
00:04:41.864 --> 00:04:43.949
Or she's being abused.

128
00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:45.158
That too.

129
00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:46.827
We'll find out more
when Dad shows up.

130
00:04:46.828 --> 00:04:48.830
Yep.
If he shows up.

131
00:04:52.041 --> 00:04:54.127
I need a hand here!

132
00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:57.671
There's the first barb out.

133
00:04:57.672 --> 00:04:59.340
All right. Javadi. you're up.

134
00:05:02.093 --> 00:05:03.927
Okay. so you're gonna
want to clamp

135
00:05:03.928 --> 00:05:06.471
where the shaft meets the barb.

136
00:05:06.472 --> 00:05:07.723
- Mm-hmm.
- Yep.

137
00:05:07.724 --> 00:05:09.683
Stabilize the skin.

138
00:05:09.684 --> 00:05:12.144
Not so close
so as to stick yourself.

139
00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:13.562
I've seen that once or twice.

140
00:05:13.563 --> 00:05:16.023
Uh. pull up at 90 degrees.

141
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:17.774
Harder.
Yep.

142
00:05:17.775 --> 00:05:19.109
Harder.

143
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:20.110
Oh.

144
00:05:20.111 --> 00:05:22.112
Do we suture those?

145
00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:23.780
Nope. just a Band-Aid.

146
00:05:23.781 --> 00:05:26.283
- Mel. we need orders.
- Right.

147
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:27.367
I got a rainbow.

148
00:05:27.368 --> 00:05:29.995
Uh. CBC...

149
00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:33.290
CMP. UA. blood alcohol.
and tox screen.

150
00:05:33.291 --> 00:05:34.708
All of the above.

151
00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:36.043
Cap. if this
young man's stable.

152
00:05:36.044 --> 00:05:37.461
can he go to Central 10 pronto?

153
00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:38.670
Double trauma at the back door.

154
00:05:38.671 --> 00:05:40.756
Okay. you heard the boss.
Let's get going.

155
00:05:40.757 --> 00:05:43.217
Today is starting to heat up.

156
00:05:46.929 --> 00:05:49.848
Mark Yee. 32-year-old
restrained driver.

157
00:05:49.849 --> 00:05:51.266
auto versus motorcycle.

158
00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:53.810
Altered with normal BP.
satting 99 on 2 liters.

159
00:05:53.811 --> 00:05:55.812
We're at
the hospital now. Mark.

160
00:05:55.813 --> 00:05:57.606
What's wrong with him?
Why isn't he talking?

161
00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:59.441
His wife. Nancy.
front-seat passenger.

162
00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:01.026
- declined transport.
- I'm fine.

163
00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:04.279
We weren't going all that fast.
The motorcycle ran the light.

164
00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:06.406
I'm Dr. Robby.
This is Dr. Al-Hashimi.

165
00:06:06.407 --> 00:06:07.866
- Nice to meet you.
- And this is Nurse Dana.

166
00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:09.117
She's our charge nurse.

167
00:06:09.118 --> 00:06:10.619
We need to look over
your husband.

168
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:12.037
Hello. Let's step over here
for a minute. hon.

169
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:13.330
Let them get to work. okay?

170
00:06:13.331 --> 00:06:15.415
Antoine. Larry.
transfer out here.

171
00:06:15.416 --> 00:06:16.833
T-1 will be open in a sec.

172
00:06:16.834 --> 00:06:18.210
Aye. aye. Cap.

173
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.463
One. two. three.

174
00:06:21.255 --> 00:06:22.297
Incoming.

175
00:06:22.298 --> 00:06:24.007
Okay. Joy. you stay with me.

176
00:06:24.008 --> 00:06:26.344
Samira. you stay
with Dr. Al-Hashimi.

177
00:06:28.221 --> 00:06:29.554
Open skull fracture.

178
00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:31.181
Tubed him
for agonal respirations.

179
00:06:31.182 --> 00:06:32.933
BP 60 palp initially.

180
00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:35.269
Started a liter of NS.
but lost his pulse en route.

181
00:06:37.146 --> 00:06:39.231
Oh. boy.
this doesn't look good.

182
00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:40.816
One. two. three.

183
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:42.651
Joy. check his pupils.

184
00:06:42.652 --> 00:06:44.028
Somebody hand me
a pair of scissors.

185
00:06:48.699 --> 00:06:50.283
8 millimeters.
Nonreactive.

186
00:06:50.284 --> 00:06:53.161
AKA blown pupils.
fixed and dilated.

187
00:06:53.162 --> 00:06:54.538
Oh.

188
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.331
Crushed skull with tons
of gray matter extravasation.

189
00:06:56.332 --> 00:06:57.874
At least it was quick.

190
00:06:57.875 --> 00:06:59.751
- No helmet?
- Nope. 'cause he took

191
00:06:59.752 --> 00:07:01.211
the PennDOT
Motorcycle Safety Course.

192
00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:02.629
Isn't that
what you took. Robby?

193
00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:05.507
Hold compressions.
Yes. but I still wear a helmet.

194
00:07:05.508 --> 00:07:07.634
- Is he a donor?
- Also nope.

195
00:07:07.635 --> 00:07:08.927
That is too bad.

196
00:07:08.928 --> 00:07:11.680
Asystole.
I think we are done here.

197
00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:13.473
- What's next door?
- The guy who hit him.

198
00:07:13.474 --> 00:07:14.891
Joy. you're with me.

199
00:07:14.892 --> 00:07:17.602
What about a moment
of reflection? I thought--

200
00:07:17.603 --> 00:07:19.354
He'll still be dead
when we get back.

201
00:07:19.355 --> 00:07:22.399
Pulse ox 99.
BP 108 over 72.

202
00:07:22.400 --> 00:07:23.483
EFAST negative.

203
00:07:23.484 --> 00:07:24.776
Hell of a lot better
than the guy next door.

204
00:07:24.777 --> 00:07:26.153
- How's the airway?
- Good volume.

205
00:07:26.154 --> 00:07:28.406
Good sats.
Gag reflex...

206
00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:30.615
Present.

207
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:31.950
- Intubate?
- Maybe.

208
00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:33.160
- Maybe not.
- Mr. Yee?

209
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:34.953
Joy. sternal rub
on his chest. like this.

210
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:36.163
Really hard. please.

211
00:07:36.164 --> 00:07:38.165
Mr. Yee?

212
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.333
Spontaneous eye movement.
Responds to pain.

213
00:07:40.334 --> 00:07:42.335
GCS is 10.
Borderline for intubation.

214
00:07:42.336 --> 00:07:45.213
No muscle tone--flaccid
paralysis in the left arm.

215
00:07:45.214 --> 00:07:46.798
- Same on the right.
- And both legs.

216
00:07:46.799 --> 00:07:48.800
Add towels to both sides of
the collar for more stability.

217
00:07:48.801 --> 00:07:51.011
Let's not make this worse.

218
00:07:51.012 --> 00:07:53.930
Pan scan with 3D
reconstruction of the spine.

219
00:07:53.931 --> 00:07:55.390
He's quadriplegic?

220
00:07:55.391 --> 00:07:57.809
If so. it's
a low cervical injury.

221
00:07:57.810 --> 00:07:59.978
- Why is that. Joy?
- Uh...

222
00:07:59.979 --> 00:08:03.899
C3. 4. and 5 helps you
breathe to stay alive.

223
00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:05.484
<i>Mr. Montrose...</i>

224
00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:08.320
you can't just be wandering
around. talking to patients.

225
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:10.155
Well. that's--
that's what I do.

226
00:08:10.156 --> 00:08:11.740
I'm a greeter at Walmart.

227
00:08:11.741 --> 00:08:15.243
I get paid to wander
and to talk to folks.

228
00:08:15.244 --> 00:08:17.537
Well. as a--
as a personal favor to me.

229
00:08:17.538 --> 00:08:20.665
can you at least stay
in your general vicinity?

230
00:08:20.666 --> 00:08:22.876
I can get you a wheelchair
while we wait for your X-rays.

231
00:08:22.877 --> 00:08:24.211
but it might take a minute.

232
00:08:24.212 --> 00:08:25.712
My dear. I cannot sit.

233
00:08:25.713 --> 00:08:27.756
My backside is killing me
from where I fell on it.

234
00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:30.342
which is an embarrassing
admission to make

235
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:33.053
to such a lovely woman.

236
00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:34.638
Well. thank you
for the compliment.

237
00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:36.431
but there's no need
to be embarrassed.

238
00:08:36.432 --> 00:08:37.933
You took a very nasty fall.

239
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:40.810
Well. then may I say that
one look in your beautiful eyes

240
00:08:40.811 --> 00:08:42.939
and I think I'm falling again.

241
00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:47.776
What a charmer.

242
00:08:47.777 --> 00:08:50.028
Just for that. I'm gonna
get you a foam donut.

243
00:08:50.029 --> 00:08:52.405
It's the eighth wonder
of the world.

244
00:08:52.406 --> 00:08:54.825
Pretty great laugh
you got there. Doc.

245
00:08:56.869 --> 00:08:59.246
Oh. God.
My witch's cackle?

246
00:08:59.247 --> 00:09:01.039
Got CT results
for Mr. Williams.

247
00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.542
Ah.

248
00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:06.963
Oh. wow.

249
00:09:08.923 --> 00:09:11.758
Okay.

250
00:09:11.759 --> 00:09:13.969
Ah.
Right on time.

251
00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:16.054
Just--just getting full.

252
00:09:16.055 --> 00:09:17.889
Yeah. I'm ready
for number five.

253
00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:19.766
- That's impressive.
- Uh-huh.

254
00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:21.977
Yeah. there's more
where that came from.

255
00:09:21.978 --> 00:09:25.772
Although. uh. my intake
is running low.

256
00:09:25.773 --> 00:09:27.566
Yeah. well. two more bottles
ought to do it.

257
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:29.526
Then we'll drain your tooth.
and we'll get you out of here

258
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:31.987
- before the fireworks tonight.
- Oh.

259
00:09:31.988 --> 00:09:33.196
Okay. Clamped.

260
00:09:33.197 --> 00:09:36.116
Ogilvie. make the change.

261
00:09:36.117 --> 00:09:38.994
- Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

262
00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:42.038
All right.
Let her rip.

263
00:09:42.039 --> 00:09:44.541
Flowing like a river.

264
00:09:44.542 --> 00:09:47.419
I love me some fireworks.

265
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:49.462
Oh. yeah?

266
00:09:49.463 --> 00:09:52.465
Shit. I-I met Mr. Zambelli...

267
00:09:52.466 --> 00:09:54.217
Lean forward.

268
00:09:54.218 --> 00:09:56.344
Many times on the field.

269
00:09:56.345 --> 00:09:59.014
Who's Mr. Zambelli?

270
00:09:59.015 --> 00:10:00.515
Son. you don't know fireworks

271
00:10:00.516 --> 00:10:03.059
if you don't know
the name Zambelli.

272
00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:05.020
He helped Pittsburgh become

273
00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:07.647
the firework capital
of America.

274
00:10:07.648 --> 00:10:09.983
You did know that. didn't you?

275
00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:11.651
- No.
- Ah.

276
00:10:11.652 --> 00:10:14.946
Y'all don't know nothing
about pyrotechnics.

277
00:10:14.947 --> 00:10:16.406
Stick to doctoring.

278
00:10:16.407 --> 00:10:18.534
Yes. will do.

279
00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:28.418
I'm sure you have
some questions.

280
00:10:28.419 --> 00:10:31.838
I know it's a lot to take in.

281
00:10:31.839 --> 00:10:34.257
It's a tumor.

282
00:10:34.258 --> 00:10:35.425
It's a brain tumor.

283
00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:38.553
Well. it's a mass.
about 4 centimeters.

284
00:10:38.554 --> 00:10:40.556
in the frontal lobe.

285
00:10:41.849 --> 00:10:43.892
Is it cancer?

286
00:10:43.893 --> 00:10:46.394
We can't say
for sure right now.

287
00:10:46.395 --> 00:10:47.854
It could be many things--

288
00:10:47.855 --> 00:10:51.024
uh. infection. inflammation.

289
00:10:51.025 --> 00:10:53.985
a benign cyst.

290
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:57.280
Is it what made me fall?

291
00:10:57.281 --> 00:10:59.116
Yeah. possibly.

292
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:03.870
We'd like to keep you here
and treat with dexamethasone.

293
00:11:03.871 --> 00:11:05.955
which is a steroid
to take down the swelling.

294
00:11:05.956 --> 00:11:07.457
- Hmm.
- And then we'll need

295
00:11:07.458 --> 00:11:10.418
a brain biopsy
to know exactly what it is.

296
00:11:10.419 --> 00:11:14.339
What. you're--you're gonna
cut open my head?

297
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:16.675
It's just a small hole.

298
00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:20.553
We'll do a-a CT-guided
stereotactical biopsy

299
00:11:20.554 --> 00:11:22.889
with a-a blunt. thin needle.

300
00:11:22.890 --> 00:11:25.725
which sounds crazy. but it's
actually pretty amazing.

301
00:11:25.726 --> 00:11:28.604
I mean. most patients
go home the next day.

302
00:11:32.441 --> 00:11:34.859
I don't know.

303
00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:38.405
What do you think I should do?

304
00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:41.866
I think this is
a pretty good plan.

305
00:11:41.867 --> 00:11:43.284
- Okay.
- Yeah?

306
00:11:43.285 --> 00:11:47.330
BP 95 over 67.

307
00:11:47.331 --> 00:11:49.332
Seems a little
on the low side.

308
00:11:49.333 --> 00:11:50.834
It is.

309
00:11:50.835 --> 00:11:53.044
Have you ever had
low blood pressure in the past?

310
00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:56.047
No. sir. My blood pressure's
always high.

311
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:59.092
Hold still. sir.
No talking while we do the EKG.

312
00:11:59.093 --> 00:12:01.720
The Hansens all run high.
except for Monty.

313
00:12:01.721 --> 00:12:04.139
- He ran low. but he's dead.
- That's not helpful.

314
00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:07.016
You want to help.
quit playing family pharmacist.

315
00:12:07.017 --> 00:12:09.477
Pooling meds is how
we've always done it.

316
00:12:09.478 --> 00:12:10.812
You put everything
in a big pile

317
00:12:10.813 --> 00:12:12.063
in the middle of the table--

318
00:12:12.064 --> 00:12:13.398
Well. look where
that got us now.

319
00:12:13.399 --> 00:12:15.525
No. I'm gonna jump in here
and echo that sharing meds

320
00:12:15.526 --> 00:12:16.693
which haven't been
prescribed to you

321
00:12:16.694 --> 00:12:17.986
is actually a real big no-no.

322
00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:19.028
How we doing on remembering

323
00:12:19.029 --> 00:12:20.447
what your brother
might've taken?

324
00:12:20.448 --> 00:12:21.614
We could call
back to the house.

325
00:12:21.615 --> 00:12:24.200
Great idea.
Okay.

326
00:12:24.201 --> 00:12:26.578
Whatever little round pill
you took. sir.

327
00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:28.663
has caused your heart rate
and blood pressure

328
00:12:28.664 --> 00:12:30.915
to drop so low.
you're at risk of fainting.

329
00:12:30.916 --> 00:12:33.084
falling. or having
a serious injury.

330
00:12:33.085 --> 00:12:34.210
Oh.

331
00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:35.837
We need to take
him back to the ER

332
00:12:35.838 --> 00:12:36.921
so he can get
a liter of fluids.

333
00:12:36.922 --> 00:12:38.256
we can check his blood tests

334
00:12:38.257 --> 00:12:39.591
and monitor his heart rate
and blood pressure

335
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:41.760
till he recovers.

336
00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.428
Pulse ox holding steady
at 99.

337
00:12:43.429 --> 00:12:44.596
Good tidal volume.

338
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.264
How you doing there. Mr. Yee?

339
00:12:46.265 --> 00:12:47.640
Scanner can take him now.

340
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:48.975
I'll check the results
from upstairs.

341
00:12:48.976 --> 00:12:51.728
- Why is he so altered?
- Could be concussion.

342
00:12:51.729 --> 00:12:53.646
Maybe a small
intracranial hemorrhage.

343
00:12:53.647 --> 00:12:56.191
All will be revealed
by the Donut of Truth.

344
00:12:56.192 --> 00:12:58.860
- Need a portable monitor.
- Joy. stay with him. please.

345
00:12:58.861 --> 00:13:00.820
See if the radiologist
can give us a STAT read.

346
00:13:00.821 --> 00:13:01.905
How is he?

347
00:13:01.906 --> 00:13:04.282
Did I hear someone
say he's paralyzed?

348
00:13:04.283 --> 00:13:06.618
There are signs of weakness
in both arms and legs.

349
00:13:06.619 --> 00:13:08.995
But before we can make
any prognosis.

350
00:13:08.996 --> 00:13:10.330
we'll need a full-body scan.

351
00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:12.665
Head CT will show us
any brain injury.

352
00:13:12.666 --> 00:13:14.834
Neck CT will show us
any spinal-cord injury.

353
00:13:14.835 --> 00:13:17.545
Chest. abdomen. pelvis will
rule out any internal bleeding.

354
00:13:17.546 --> 00:13:18.630
Oh. my God.

355
00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:21.508
The scans should only take
about 15 minutes.

356
00:13:21.509 --> 00:13:24.302
In the meantime. perhaps you'd
let us look you over as well?

357
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:26.596
I'm fine.
The medics checked me.

358
00:13:26.597 --> 00:13:29.140
I just want to stay
with my husband.

359
00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:31.392
Well. you can't go
into the CT with him.

360
00:13:31.393 --> 00:13:33.645
but you can wait just outside
if you like.

361
00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:34.938
- Excuse me.
- Princess. this is Nancy.

362
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:36.564
Mrs. Yee is gonna go
with her husband to CT.

363
00:13:36.565 --> 00:13:37.690
Will you show her where to go?

364
00:13:37.691 --> 00:13:40.319
- Sure. Come on in.
- Thank you.

365
00:13:42.154 --> 00:13:44.030
So what's the plan now?

366
00:13:44.031 --> 00:13:46.199
Keep observing me
in my natural habitat?

367
00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:47.617
No telling
what I might do next.

368
00:13:47.618 --> 00:13:49.202
I think I've got the gist.

369
00:13:49.203 --> 00:13:51.329
How about we each take a lap
and meet here

370
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.831
when Mr. Yee is back from CT?

371
00:13:52.832 --> 00:13:54.749
Splitting up so soon?

372
00:13:54.750 --> 00:13:57.919
You're free to see
other people. Dr. Robinavitch.

373
00:13:57.920 --> 00:14:00.631
I'm looking for cooperation.
not commitment.

374
00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:07.303
So you bandaged
the burn yourself?

375
00:14:07.304 --> 00:14:09.097
Oh. no. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no--

376
00:14:09.098 --> 00:14:11.182
Ma'am. you're--you're making
it difficult for me

377
00:14:11.183 --> 00:14:12.892
to see under this dressing.

378
00:14:12.893 --> 00:14:16.229
- Is that a tablecloth?
- Part of a window curtain.

379
00:14:16.230 --> 00:14:17.605
Cleaner than tablecloth.

380
00:14:17.606 --> 00:14:19.315
I'll wait for the doctor.
Thank you.

381
00:14:19.316 --> 00:14:22.735
May I ask how this happened?

382
00:14:22.736 --> 00:14:24.487
For weeks on end.
the kids with their

383
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:26.781
<i>guchnyy</i> firecrackers.
going all day and night.

384
00:14:26.782 --> 00:14:28.867
Oh. i-is this
a firecracker burn?

385
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:31.870
No. sweetie.
this is from the full samovar

386
00:14:31.871 --> 00:14:34.789
I drop on the floor
when the sh--

387
00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:37.417
the firecrackers
started going on again.

388
00:14:37.418 --> 00:14:39.377
I'm sorry.
What's a samovar?

389
00:14:39.378 --> 00:14:42.630
It is a big metal urn
for coffee or tea.

390
00:14:42.631 --> 00:14:44.757
They can get super-duper hot.

391
00:14:44.758 --> 00:14:47.010
and I was never allowed
to touch ours.

392
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:48.428
Uh. hello. Mrs. Kovalenko.

393
00:14:48.429 --> 00:14:49.721
My name is
Dr. Michael Robinavitch.

394
00:14:49.722 --> 00:14:51.389
Everybody calls me Dr. Robby.

395
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:54.392
- Robinavitch? Jewish?
- You guessed it.

396
00:14:54.393 --> 00:14:57.896
And I see that you are
here today for a burn.

397
00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.314
Why don't we take a look?

398
00:14:59.315 --> 00:15:00.899
Oh. not married?

399
00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:02.526
No. I'm not married.

400
00:15:03.777 --> 00:15:05.236
Do you attend synagogue?

401
00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:08.197
Uh. not for a while.

402
00:15:08.198 --> 00:15:12.160
I mean. High Holidays mostly.

403
00:15:12.161 --> 00:15:13.328
Where?

404
00:15:13.329 --> 00:15:14.996
Ooh.

405
00:15:14.997 --> 00:15:17.290
What did you put on this?

406
00:15:17.291 --> 00:15:18.875
- Where?
- On your burn.

407
00:15:18.876 --> 00:15:21.127
- Is this honey?
- Yes. honey.

408
00:15:21.128 --> 00:15:23.129
Where do you go on holy days?

409
00:15:23.130 --> 00:15:26.132
Uh. my grandparents. um--

410
00:15:26.133 --> 00:15:27.842
I grew up
going to Rodef Shalom.

411
00:15:27.843 --> 00:15:28.843
You?

412
00:15:28.844 --> 00:15:31.138
Tree of Life.

413
00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:34.349
They're rebuilding.

414
00:15:34.350 --> 00:15:36.768
Yes. something new.

415
00:15:36.769 --> 00:15:40.271
Remember. Rebuild. Renew.

416
00:15:40.272 --> 00:15:42.650
That's the slogan.

417
00:15:44.693 --> 00:15:47.487
I'm sorry.
did you say "honey"?

418
00:15:47.488 --> 00:15:49.656
You think honey's funny?

419
00:15:49.657 --> 00:15:51.658
Works like a charm.

420
00:15:51.659 --> 00:15:53.785
My father kept bees.
I know.

421
00:15:53.786 --> 00:15:57.080
If the honey is medical grade
and the burns are not too bad.

422
00:15:57.081 --> 00:15:59.207
honey actually does have
some antibacterial

423
00:15:59.208 --> 00:16:00.792
and anti-inflammatory
properties.

424
00:16:00.793 --> 00:16:03.378
However. these burns
are very deep in some places.

425
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:05.755
They're going
to need debridement.

426
00:16:05.756 --> 00:16:08.758
I'm glad you came in.

427
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.593
That's what I thought.

428
00:16:10.594 --> 00:16:14.597
I was hoping no.
but I figured as much.

429
00:16:14.598 --> 00:16:15.723
Not to worry.

430
00:16:15.724 --> 00:16:18.559
We are gonna have you
patched up and home

431
00:16:18.560 --> 00:16:20.228
in time for dinner
and fireworks.

432
00:16:20.229 --> 00:16:22.146
No.

433
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:23.648
No more fireworks.

434
00:16:23.649 --> 00:16:24.899
No.

435
00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:26.025
Okay.

436
00:16:26.026 --> 00:16:30.321
Anyone here treating
Kylie Connors?

437
00:16:30.322 --> 00:16:31.823
She's my daughter.

438
00:16:31.824 --> 00:16:33.908
She's nine.
I'm Benny Connors.

439
00:16:33.909 --> 00:16:36.369
Mr. Connors. I'm Dr. Santos.

440
00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:37.745
I'm treating Kylie.

441
00:16:37.746 --> 00:16:39.330
Is she okay?
Can I see her?

442
00:16:39.331 --> 00:16:41.290
My--my girlfriend. Gina.
says she got a cut on her chin?

443
00:16:41.291 --> 00:16:42.375
Yeah. I can take you to her.

444
00:16:42.376 --> 00:16:44.127
She has a small
laceration on her chin.

445
00:16:44.128 --> 00:16:46.379
but it was easily repaired
with medical superglue.

446
00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.548
- so no stitches necessary.
- Okay.

447
00:16:48.549 --> 00:16:51.092
She chipped a tooth.
but it's a baby tooth.

448
00:16:51.093 --> 00:16:52.885
so it won't need dental work.

449
00:16:52.886 --> 00:16:54.804
All right.
well. that's a relief.

450
00:16:54.805 --> 00:16:57.306
Has Kylie had
any previous injuries?

451
00:16:57.307 --> 00:16:58.975
Uh. yeah.

452
00:16:58.976 --> 00:17:01.227
She. um--she broke
her wrist last year.

453
00:17:01.228 --> 00:17:02.854
She was skateboarding.

454
00:17:02.855 --> 00:17:06.065
Dana. if you could get Dylan
to come to North 1.

455
00:17:06.066 --> 00:17:08.151
- and Ahmad.
- You bet.

456
00:17:08.152 --> 00:17:10.486
Okay. I got it now.
One. two. three.

457
00:17:10.487 --> 00:17:11.738
Daddy. you came.

458
00:17:11.739 --> 00:17:13.573
Baby. what's going on. huh?

459
00:17:13.574 --> 00:17:15.283
My tooth broke.
and my chin got cut.

460
00:17:15.284 --> 00:17:16.618
Oh. no.

461
00:17:18.537 --> 00:17:19.746
What happened?

462
00:17:19.747 --> 00:17:21.998
She was running
up the stairs.

463
00:17:21.999 --> 00:17:24.667
- Gina was chasing me.
- We were playing.

464
00:17:24.668 --> 00:17:27.211
As I was saying. Mr. Connors.
the laceration is pretty minor.

465
00:17:27.212 --> 00:17:28.254
On the stairs?

466
00:17:28.255 --> 00:17:30.423
- It was an accident.
- Perhaps we can--

467
00:17:30.424 --> 00:17:32.008
An accident
that wouldn't have happened

468
00:17:32.009 --> 00:17:33.342
if you weren't running
up the stairs.

469
00:17:33.343 --> 00:17:34.510
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

470
00:17:34.511 --> 00:17:36.971
This is the last thing
that I need right now.

471
00:17:36.972 --> 00:17:38.681
is her mother finding out
that she got hurt

472
00:17:38.682 --> 00:17:40.308
- when she's with you.
- It was an accident.

473
00:17:40.309 --> 00:17:41.851
And before you get
all high and mighty.

474
00:17:41.852 --> 00:17:43.811
- I've got questions of my own.
- Like what?

475
00:17:43.812 --> 00:17:45.146
Hey. Mr. Connors.

476
00:17:45.147 --> 00:17:47.023
I'm sorry. I meant to be here
when you arrived.

477
00:17:47.024 --> 00:17:48.983
I'm Dylan Easton.
I'm with Social Services.

478
00:17:48.984 --> 00:17:50.151
We have insurance.
Thank you.

479
00:17:50.152 --> 00:17:51.819
Perhaps we can step outside
and chat for a second?

480
00:17:51.820 --> 00:17:53.738
I can fill you in
on where we are.

481
00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:55.615
Hey. uh. Jesse. do you want
to keep Kylie entertained

482
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.283
- for a few minutes while I...
- Absolutely.

483
00:17:57.284 --> 00:17:58.326
Borrow her dad?

484
00:17:58.327 --> 00:17:59.494
We'll just head down
to the family room.

485
00:17:59.495 --> 00:18:01.704
It's a little quieter there.

486
00:18:01.705 --> 00:18:03.498
Why do I got to talk
to a social worker?

487
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:06.000
Anytime a child is injured.
we have some standard questions

488
00:18:06.001 --> 00:18:07.502
that we ask parents
and caregivers.

489
00:18:07.503 --> 00:18:10.671
Good. That's fine. Great.
Ask me here.

490
00:18:10.672 --> 00:18:14.217
Well. we noticed
some bruising on Kylie's body.

491
00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:17.637
some old. some new.
on her back and legs.

492
00:18:17.638 --> 00:18:19.847
- Any idea how she got those?
- Yeah. soccer.

493
00:18:19.848 --> 00:18:21.057
She plays for a club team.

494
00:18:21.058 --> 00:18:22.350
They're. you know.
little girls.

495
00:18:22.351 --> 00:18:24.435
but they play like they're
in "The Hunger Games."

496
00:18:24.436 --> 00:18:26.521
Well. I understand
that you and Kylie do

497
00:18:26.522 --> 00:18:29.440
a fair amount of roughhousing.

498
00:18:29.441 --> 00:18:31.442
What?

499
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:34.153
I'm sorry.
Are you fucking kidding me?

500
00:18:34.154 --> 00:18:35.321
Where are you going with this?

501
00:18:35.322 --> 00:18:36.614
Are you saying
that I hurt my daughter?

502
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:37.907
Mr. Connors.
nobody's saying that--

503
00:18:37.908 --> 00:18:39.033
Oh. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no. no.

504
00:18:39.034 --> 00:18:40.243
- Gina!
- Mr. Connors--

505
00:18:40.244 --> 00:18:41.619
Just--just--Gina!

506
00:18:41.620 --> 00:18:42.620
Sir. take a breath.

507
00:18:42.621 --> 00:18:43.788
Gina. what did you say
to them?

508
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:45.623
Nothing.
I said that you're a great dad.

509
00:18:45.624 --> 00:18:47.125
Okay. What else?

510
00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:48.626
That you guys
like to wrestle.

511
00:18:48.627 --> 00:18:49.836
- Jesus Christ.
- What?

512
00:18:49.837 --> 00:18:51.337
They wanted to know where
all her bruises are from.

513
00:18:51.338 --> 00:18:53.214
Who the fuck are you to talk
about me and my daughter?

514
00:18:53.215 --> 00:18:54.757
- Who the fuck am I?
- Yeah. that's what I'm asking.

515
00:18:54.758 --> 00:18:55.925
Who the fuck am I?

516
00:18:55.926 --> 00:18:57.301
Hey. big man. take
one more fucking step--

517
00:18:57.302 --> 00:18:59.720
Hey. that's enough.
You need to calm down.

518
00:18:59.721 --> 00:19:01.722
Hey. everybody.
back the fuck up!

519
00:19:01.723 --> 00:19:03.099
Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

520
00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:06.185
Kylie's platelets
are only 9.000.

521
00:19:06.186 --> 00:19:08.187
What does that mean?

522
00:19:08.188 --> 00:19:11.065
It's--it's not what we thought.

523
00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:13.401
It's probably ITP.

524
00:19:13.402 --> 00:19:15.736
What the hell is ITP?

525
00:19:15.737 --> 00:19:17.948
Something we can treat.

526
00:19:24.163 --> 00:19:26.789
- You feel that?
- Mm. no.

527
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:28.457
Excellent.

528
00:19:28.458 --> 00:19:30.376
This is looking very good.

529
00:19:30.377 --> 00:19:32.337
Ah. Tell Mr. Kovalenko.

530
00:19:36.049 --> 00:19:37.341
Mrs. Kovalenko?

531
00:19:37.342 --> 00:19:39.260
Yes?
Yana. please.

532
00:19:39.261 --> 00:19:43.222
Yana. you mentioned
that you dropped the samovar

533
00:19:43.223 --> 00:19:46.684
when you heard firecrackers.

534
00:19:46.685 --> 00:19:47.686
Yeah.

535
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:54.525
I was on my way inside--

536
00:19:54.526 --> 00:19:57.653
October 27. 2018--

537
00:19:57.654 --> 00:20:00.532
to the synagogue
when the shooting started.

538
00:20:05.287 --> 00:20:08.247
There was nothing I could do.

539
00:20:08.248 --> 00:20:09.874
I went in...

540
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:12.418
after the police arrived.

541
00:20:12.419 --> 00:20:14.463
I felt I had to.

542
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:18.591
I'm better now.

543
00:20:18.592 --> 00:20:21.052
But...

544
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:24.430
New Year's Eve. Fourth of July.

545
00:20:24.431 --> 00:20:27.934
when--when kids have
their fireworks

546
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:30.687
and firecrackers. I--

547
00:20:32.898 --> 00:20:35.734
There is no clock
on how long it takes.

548
00:20:37.361 --> 00:20:39.070
No clock.

549
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:41.865
You must be joking.

550
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:45.326
- Robby?
- Yep.

551
00:20:45.327 --> 00:20:47.536
- Mark Yee is back from CT.
- Oh. okay.

552
00:20:47.537 --> 00:20:49.038
Um. Perlah. why don't we go
ahead and see if we can put

553
00:20:49.039 --> 00:20:50.831
a nonstick dressing on this?

554
00:20:50.832 --> 00:20:53.125
And I will come back.
and we can discuss

555
00:20:53.126 --> 00:20:54.543
aftercare instructions.

556
00:20:54.544 --> 00:20:56.045
Yeah. you got it. boss.

557
00:20:56.046 --> 00:20:58.090
Thank you. Doctor.

558
00:21:10.352 --> 00:21:12.895
Vitals stable.
Pulse ox holding at 99.

559
00:21:12.896 --> 00:21:14.898
Okay.
Heart and lungs look good.

560
00:21:17.109 --> 00:21:19.443
- Dr. Mohan.
- Dr. Robby?

561
00:21:19.444 --> 00:21:20.612
Yeah?

562
00:21:22.739 --> 00:21:25.324
Please make him be okay.

563
00:21:25.325 --> 00:21:27.243
I can assure you that we
are gonna do absolutely--

564
00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:29.912
Everything you can.
I know.

565
00:21:29.913 --> 00:21:31.497
God. this is all my fault.

566
00:21:31.498 --> 00:21:34.417
- Mrs. Yee--
- Oh. he's been so stressed.

567
00:21:34.418 --> 00:21:36.794
So I planned this weekend away
at Seven Springs.

568
00:21:36.795 --> 00:21:39.380
but he didn't want to go
because of work.

569
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:42.508
So we fought
this whole morning.

570
00:21:42.509 --> 00:21:44.969
And then I...

571
00:21:44.970 --> 00:21:48.264
I said awful things.

572
00:21:48.265 --> 00:21:50.266
Those can't be the last words
we say to each other.

573
00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:51.892
Doctor. please.

574
00:21:51.893 --> 00:21:54.854
Good news.
CT looks normal.

575
00:21:54.855 --> 00:21:56.564
No bleeding inside the skull.

576
00:21:56.565 --> 00:21:59.400
C-spine. no fractures seen.

577
00:21:59.401 --> 00:22:01.819
- He didn't break his neck?
- Then why is he paralyzed?

578
00:22:01.820 --> 00:22:03.446
You can have spinal injuries

579
00:22:03.447 --> 00:22:05.239
without
radiologic abnormalities.

580
00:22:05.240 --> 00:22:08.659
Sometimes it doesn't show up
on CT. only on MRI.

581
00:22:08.660 --> 00:22:10.454
Dr. Mohan.

582
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:14.416
Are you sure?

583
00:22:17.461 --> 00:22:19.295
Okay.

584
00:22:19.296 --> 00:22:21.380
Critical potassium level. 1.2.

585
00:22:21.381 --> 00:22:22.965
Wow.

586
00:22:22.966 --> 00:22:24.592
- Okay.
- That's crazy low.

587
00:22:24.593 --> 00:22:26.635
Uh. extremely low potassium
with generalized weakness

588
00:22:26.636 --> 00:22:28.554
and no cervical injury.

589
00:22:28.555 --> 00:22:29.889
We may be looking at--

590
00:22:29.890 --> 00:22:31.724
Hypokalemic
periodic paralysis.

591
00:22:31.725 --> 00:22:32.850
What is that?

592
00:22:32.851 --> 00:22:34.435
It's a rare condition
where potassium gets shifted

593
00:22:34.436 --> 00:22:36.604
into the cells.
causing profound weakness.

594
00:22:36.605 --> 00:22:37.813
just like paralysis.

595
00:22:37.814 --> 00:22:39.523
- Will he get better?
- Yes.

596
00:22:39.524 --> 00:22:41.233
Back to normal in a few hours.

597
00:22:41.234 --> 00:22:42.568
In a f--

598
00:22:42.569 --> 00:22:45.321
Replete slowly.
10 MEQ of KCl--

599
00:22:45.322 --> 00:22:47.323
Thank you so much.

600
00:22:47.324 --> 00:22:48.866
Did you hear that. Mark?

601
00:22:48.867 --> 00:22:52.620
Oh. baby.
you're gonna get better.

602
00:22:52.621 --> 00:22:54.872
Oh. baby.

603
00:22:54.873 --> 00:22:56.707
All right. DD.
Hey. come on now. man.

604
00:22:56.708 --> 00:22:58.626
Oh. how you doing. Duante?

605
00:22:58.627 --> 00:23:00.211
- Fine.
- Great.

606
00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:01.629
If you're fine. you go home.

607
00:23:01.630 --> 00:23:02.713
- Really?
- Yeah.

608
00:23:02.714 --> 00:23:05.841
Mm-mm.
Hey. tell them.

609
00:23:05.842 --> 00:23:08.427
Me and my sister
were making bracelets.

610
00:23:08.428 --> 00:23:12.431
and I put beads up my nose.

611
00:23:12.432 --> 00:23:13.933
How many?

612
00:23:13.934 --> 00:23:15.351
One on each side.

613
00:23:15.352 --> 00:23:18.020
I got to ask--
why'd you stick them up there?

614
00:23:18.021 --> 00:23:19.730
See how many will fit?

615
00:23:19.731 --> 00:23:21.649
To shoot them out
like rockets.

616
00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:22.733
Mm.

617
00:23:22.734 --> 00:23:24.110
But I breathed in.

618
00:23:24.111 --> 00:23:27.113
and they went deeper
and now won't come out.

619
00:23:27.114 --> 00:23:28.948
Did you try anything at home?

620
00:23:28.949 --> 00:23:30.616
Yeah. I tried blowing
in his mouth.

621
00:23:30.617 --> 00:23:32.326
but just got a little snot
on my cheek.

622
00:23:32.327 --> 00:23:33.494
"A" for effort. Dad.

623
00:23:33.495 --> 00:23:36.205
Okay. we need to take a look
with a little flashlight.

624
00:23:36.206 --> 00:23:38.082
- Okay?
- Okay.

625
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:39.625
This is what I have
to look forward to?

626
00:23:39.626 --> 00:23:41.919
This and so much more.

627
00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:44.547
Red bead below
the inferior turbinate.

628
00:23:44.548 --> 00:23:47.007
I...

629
00:23:47.008 --> 00:23:48.426
got a blue one.

630
00:23:48.427 --> 00:23:51.053
Afrin. benzocaine.
Katz extractor?

631
00:23:51.054 --> 00:23:53.180
Yep. Dad. looks like we got
to go up and get them.

632
00:23:53.181 --> 00:23:55.891
- No way he's sitting still.
- Oh. he'll be numbed up.

633
00:23:55.892 --> 00:23:57.101
You don't know this child.

634
00:23:57.102 --> 00:24:00.104
Hey. Duante.
you like video games?

635
00:24:00.105 --> 00:24:01.981
Everybody does.

636
00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:04.233
We have a 3D video game.

637
00:24:04.234 --> 00:24:06.111
- Yeah.
- Cool.

638
00:24:10.782 --> 00:24:13.659
That's KCl and saline
at 10 MEQ per hour.

639
00:24:13.660 --> 00:24:15.786
We avoid dextrose
because the insulin response

640
00:24:15.787 --> 00:24:17.163
drops the K even more.

641
00:24:17.164 --> 00:24:19.999
If it's genetic. why didn't
it happen when he was a kid?

642
00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.376
It usually starts
after the teen years.

643
00:24:22.377 --> 00:24:23.502
And it can be intermittent.

644
00:24:23.503 --> 00:24:26.589
Sometimes it's triggered
by intense exercise or stress.

645
00:24:26.590 --> 00:24:28.591
We've been married
eight years.

646
00:24:28.592 --> 00:24:30.759
We've had fights.
He's never collapsed.

647
00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:32.261
If his thyroid
gets overactive.

648
00:24:32.262 --> 00:24:34.096
that brings it on
later in life.

649
00:24:34.097 --> 00:24:36.682
I ordered TSH. T3. T4.

650
00:24:36.683 --> 00:24:38.935
So now we just wait?

651
00:24:41.229 --> 00:24:42.605
Bag him.
Starting compressions.

652
00:24:42.606 --> 00:24:45.232
- Charge to 200.
- What is happening?

653
00:24:45.233 --> 00:24:47.234
Low potassium
can harm electrical activity

654
00:24:47.235 --> 00:24:48.819
- in the heart.
- Charged.

655
00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:50.821
- Clear.
- Clear.

656
00:24:50.822 --> 00:24:52.616
Resuming compressions.

657
00:24:54.159 --> 00:24:58.078
- So your little girl was ITP?
- Go figure.

658
00:24:58.079 --> 00:25:00.623
Nothing like a zebra
to kick-start your morning.

659
00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:03.250
Well. it's better
than the alternative.

660
00:25:03.251 --> 00:25:04.835
True.

661
00:25:04.836 --> 00:25:07.046
ITP.

662
00:25:07.047 --> 00:25:09.548
So that's. uh. intra--

663
00:25:09.549 --> 00:25:11.217
Immune thrombocytopenia.

664
00:25:11.218 --> 00:25:14.720
Used to be called idiopathic
thrombocytopenic purpura.

665
00:25:14.721 --> 00:25:16.555
Know what "idiopathic" means?

666
00:25:16.556 --> 00:25:18.641
That we don't know
the exact cause.

667
00:25:18.642 --> 00:25:20.518
It means the patient
is pathetic

668
00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:22.938
and the doctor is an idiot.

669
00:25:24.523 --> 00:25:26.398
Just checked
on baby Jane Doe.

670
00:25:26.399 --> 00:25:29.109
Looking good.
Taking formula well.

671
00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:30.945
We're here
to take a statement.

672
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:33.739
We're looking
for a Tony Chinchiolo.

673
00:25:33.740 --> 00:25:37.326
Yo!
Right over here. boys!

674
00:25:37.327 --> 00:25:39.286
Well. officers.

675
00:25:39.287 --> 00:25:41.664
Heard you had some trouble
over at the campus library.

676
00:25:41.665 --> 00:25:43.999
Shit.
Let me just say--

677
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:46.627
new appreciation
for what you guys do every day.

678
00:25:46.628 --> 00:25:49.129
Frickin' junkie jungle. right?

679
00:25:49.130 --> 00:25:51.298
At the campus library?

680
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:52.550
Yeah.

681
00:25:52.551 --> 00:25:53.842
Thumb and forefinger
make a C.

682
00:25:53.843 --> 00:25:55.553
Bottom three fingers make an E
for jaw lift.

683
00:25:55.554 --> 00:25:57.596
One breath every five seconds.
Come here. try it.

684
00:25:57.597 --> 00:25:59.473
About two minutes
since defibrillation.

685
00:25:59.474 --> 00:26:02.601
- Holding compressions.
- Normal sinus.

686
00:26:02.602 --> 00:26:04.770
Carotid. Strong carotid.
Okay. let's try for BP.

687
00:26:04.771 --> 00:26:06.397
Why don't we check
after the shock?

688
00:26:06.398 --> 00:26:08.315
2024 ACLS guidelines.

689
00:26:08.316 --> 00:26:10.317
Patients can remain pulseless
for a little bit.

690
00:26:10.318 --> 00:26:11.819
even after successful defib.

691
00:26:11.820 --> 00:26:14.321
He came back with one shock.
That's as good as it gets.

692
00:26:14.322 --> 00:26:16.740
- 104 over 68.
- Good squeeze. Good EF.

693
00:26:16.741 --> 00:26:18.784
Spontaneous respirations.
Okay. let's lift him up.

694
00:26:18.785 --> 00:26:21.161
He's breathing on his own--
excellent sign.

695
00:26:21.162 --> 00:26:22.496
Oh. God.

696
00:26:22.497 --> 00:26:25.958
- Can I touch him?
- Of course.

697
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:27.334
Oh. Mark.

698
00:26:27.335 --> 00:26:30.379
Hey.

699
00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:32.172
Oh. shit.

700
00:26:32.173 --> 00:26:33.507
We need a gurney!

701
00:26:33.508 --> 00:26:35.342
Nancy?

702
00:26:35.343 --> 00:26:38.596
Mrs. Yee?

703
00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:40.097
Weak carotid.
Shallow breaths.

704
00:26:40.098 --> 00:26:41.932
Did she vasovagal
from stress?

705
00:26:41.933 --> 00:26:43.100
Can't assume that.

706
00:26:43.101 --> 00:26:44.935
Positive seat belt si--
oh. shit.

707
00:26:44.936 --> 00:26:46.645
Hang two units of O-neg
on the rapid infuser.

708
00:26:46.646 --> 00:26:48.230
Somebody call Garcia.
Shit.

709
00:26:48.231 --> 00:26:50.065
We really should have insisted
on examining her.

710
00:26:50.066 --> 00:26:51.400
Okay. I got the head.

711
00:26:51.401 --> 00:26:53.694
Platelets are these
tiny things in the blood

712
00:26:53.695 --> 00:26:55.279
that help it clot.

713
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:58.699
And thrombocytopenia is fancy
for "low platelets."

714
00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:01.160
which explains why your skin
bruises so easily.

715
00:27:01.161 --> 00:27:02.411
And what causes it?

716
00:27:02.412 --> 00:27:04.496
It's actually
her immune system

717
00:27:04.497 --> 00:27:06.540
that's causing
the destruction of platelets.

718
00:27:06.541 --> 00:27:08.542
Sometimes
it's a triggered response

719
00:27:08.543 --> 00:27:11.879
to. uh. an environmental factor
or virus.

720
00:27:11.880 --> 00:27:14.840
<i>And what's the treatment?
What are you giving her?</i>

721
00:27:14.841 --> 00:27:17.426
We'll be treating her
with high-dose steroids

722
00:27:17.427 --> 00:27:20.346
to suppress the immune system
and IV immunoglobulin.

723
00:27:20.347 --> 00:27:23.140
which reduces the destruction
of the platelets in the spleen.

724
00:27:23.141 --> 00:27:24.433
Can I go home?

725
00:27:24.434 --> 00:27:26.435
You're gonna have to stay
in the hospital

726
00:27:26.436 --> 00:27:28.103
for about three days

727
00:27:28.104 --> 00:27:30.439
to make sure
that the treatment is working.

728
00:27:30.440 --> 00:27:32.149
Okay. Okay.

729
00:27:32.150 --> 00:27:34.151
So when can she get
a room in the hospital?

730
00:27:34.152 --> 00:27:35.819
That is
an excellent question.

731
00:27:35.820 --> 00:27:37.404
I'm going to see
if I can make that happen

732
00:27:37.405 --> 00:27:38.530
sooner rather than later.

733
00:27:38.531 --> 00:27:40.449
- but it might take a while.
- Okay.

734
00:27:40.450 --> 00:27:42.451
<i>GPS says I should be there
by 11:00.</i>

735
00:27:42.452 --> 00:27:45.245
Do you have any other
questions for me. ma'am?

736
00:27:45.246 --> 00:27:48.040
<i>No. I'm sure I will.
but I'll let you go for now.</i>

737
00:27:48.041 --> 00:27:49.375
<i>Thank you. Benny.</i>

738
00:27:49.376 --> 00:27:50.584
All right.
I'll see you when you get here.

739
00:27:50.585 --> 00:27:52.252
<i>See you soon. baby.
I love you.</i>

740
00:27:52.253 --> 00:27:55.090
Bye. Mom.
Love you too.

741
00:27:56.424 --> 00:27:58.258
There you are.

742
00:27:58.259 --> 00:27:59.593
And there you are.

743
00:27:59.594 --> 00:28:02.554
Don't try to charm me.
You promised to stay put.

744
00:28:02.555 --> 00:28:04.264
I was going
to come right back.

745
00:28:04.265 --> 00:28:06.100
My backside is killing me.

746
00:28:06.101 --> 00:28:09.353
I need to keep moving.
or I get all achy and stiff.

747
00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:12.439
Well. I got you
this foam donut to sit on

748
00:28:12.440 --> 00:28:15.317
- while we wait for your X-rays.
- Hmm.

749
00:28:15.318 --> 00:28:17.820
Dr. Hazel Eyes. it says here

750
00:28:17.821 --> 00:28:22.741
that it's only supposed to take
an hour or two for an X-ray.

751
00:28:22.742 --> 00:28:25.661
Well. the patient passport
holiday edition

752
00:28:25.662 --> 00:28:27.371
would better reflect reality.

753
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:29.665
It could be double that.

754
00:28:29.666 --> 00:28:31.458
There's no need for reality.

755
00:28:31.459 --> 00:28:33.752
We romantics...

756
00:28:33.753 --> 00:28:37.256
prefer <i>la reve.</i> the dream.

757
00:28:37.257 --> 00:28:38.882
We do. do we?

758
00:28:38.883 --> 00:28:40.885
<i>Oui.</i>

759
00:28:49.602 --> 00:28:50.603
Right.

760
00:28:54.232 --> 00:28:56.483
Hey. save a dance for me.

761
00:28:56.484 --> 00:28:59.111
Uh. yeah. okay. I will.

762
00:28:59.112 --> 00:29:00.487
- Dr. McKay?
- Yes.

763
00:29:00.488 --> 00:29:01.739
This is Gretchen Williams.

764
00:29:01.740 --> 00:29:03.615
- Actually. it's Lambdin.
- Ah.

765
00:29:03.616 --> 00:29:05.826
You called about my
ex-husband. Michael Williams.

766
00:29:05.827 --> 00:29:07.953
Yeah. Yes. yes.
Thank you for coming in.

767
00:29:07.954 --> 00:29:10.247
You were. um. listed
as his emergency contact.

768
00:29:10.248 --> 00:29:11.623
Yeah. I don't know why.

769
00:29:11.624 --> 00:29:14.376
We have been divorced
for years.

770
00:29:14.377 --> 00:29:15.711
Is he all right?

771
00:29:15.712 --> 00:29:18.881
He's--he's going
through a lot right now.

772
00:29:18.882 --> 00:29:20.550
Would you like to see him?

773
00:29:22.552 --> 00:29:23.802
Uh. okay.

774
00:29:23.803 --> 00:29:27.556
Leo. can you zoom in and please
hold it a little steadier?

775
00:29:27.557 --> 00:29:29.100
<i>Okay.</i>

776
00:29:31.352 --> 00:29:32.770
Okay.

777
00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:34.396
Atorvastatin.

778
00:29:34.397 --> 00:29:36.023
Simvastatin.

779
00:29:36.024 --> 00:29:37.316
Ezetimibe.

780
00:29:37.317 --> 00:29:39.860
Those are all
high-cholesterol medications.

781
00:29:39.861 --> 00:29:41.570
Can you go to the right?

782
00:29:41.571 --> 00:29:43.864
Lisinopril.

783
00:29:43.865 --> 00:29:45.866
Losartan. Propranolol.

784
00:29:45.867 --> 00:29:47.868
Wait. wait. that's it.

785
00:29:47.869 --> 00:29:49.369
Wendy's pile.

786
00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:50.579
Yellowish bottle.

787
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:52.706
little. round blue pills.
just like I said.

788
00:29:52.707 --> 00:29:54.750
- Propranolol?
- Bingo. little lady.

789
00:29:54.751 --> 00:29:57.211
Okay. yeah. well. this makes
a lot of sense now.

790
00:29:57.212 --> 00:30:01.215
Um. propranolol is a
high-blood-pressure medication.

791
00:30:01.216 --> 00:30:04.092
Those are 20 milligrams each.

792
00:30:04.093 --> 00:30:06.261
and the starting dose
is 40 mgs.

793
00:30:06.262 --> 00:30:08.055
How many pills did you take?

794
00:30:08.056 --> 00:30:10.933
No. ma'am. I-I went
just before I came here.

795
00:30:10.934 --> 00:30:12.643
Dad.

796
00:30:12.644 --> 00:30:15.395
Um--pill--how many pills
did you take?

797
00:30:15.396 --> 00:30:20.192
Oh. uh.
I think four. maybe five.

798
00:30:20.193 --> 00:30:22.027
That is a lot.
Okay.

799
00:30:22.028 --> 00:30:24.279
Full stomach. mind you.

800
00:30:24.280 --> 00:30:27.491
Well. um. the good news is.
it has a short half-life.

801
00:30:27.492 --> 00:30:30.118
so. um. we're gonna need
to keep you

802
00:30:30.119 --> 00:30:31.787
for about four hours
to monitor.

803
00:30:31.788 --> 00:30:34.039
But then you'll be able
to rejoin

804
00:30:34.040 --> 00:30:36.041
for all the late-afternoon
festivities.

805
00:30:36.042 --> 00:30:38.502
- All right.
- Whoo!

806
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:40.254
Unit 3 and 4 running in.

807
00:30:40.255 --> 00:30:42.130
BP 84 over 56.
Heart rate 112.

808
00:30:42.131 --> 00:30:43.924
Free fluid's
much bigger than before.

809
00:30:43.925 --> 00:30:45.968
She's not turning the corner.
OR is holding a room.

810
00:30:45.969 --> 00:30:47.553
I'll let the husband know.

811
00:30:47.554 --> 00:30:48.887
Why did you guys wait
so long to check her?

812
00:30:48.888 --> 00:30:50.681
Good vitals in the field.
No distress.

813
00:30:50.682 --> 00:30:52.015
She refused to sign in.

814
00:30:52.016 --> 00:30:53.392
You should have
convinced her.

815
00:30:53.393 --> 00:30:54.768
20/20 hindsight.
She was stable.

816
00:30:54.769 --> 00:30:55.853
Until she wasn't.

817
00:30:55.854 --> 00:30:57.646
Next time. I'll use
my X-ray vision goggles.

818
00:30:57.647 --> 00:30:59.648
Let's get her upstairs.

819
00:30:59.649 --> 00:31:02.401
Got to do an accu-check
on my DKA patient.

820
00:31:02.402 --> 00:31:04.236
Thanks for the backup.

821
00:31:04.237 --> 00:31:05.989
Anytime.

822
00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:12.203
Now. try and lift
your arm. Mark.

823
00:31:14.205 --> 00:31:16.164
I'm trying.
Can't do it.

824
00:31:16.165 --> 00:31:20.669
But you are getting stronger.
and your speech is improving.

825
00:31:20.670 --> 00:31:23.005
How did I lose
so much potassium?

826
00:31:23.006 --> 00:31:26.300
You didn't lose it.
It got shifted into cells.

827
00:31:26.301 --> 00:31:28.552
When it comes back.
you'll return to normal.

828
00:31:28.553 --> 00:31:29.803
Where's Nancy?

829
00:31:29.804 --> 00:31:31.847
She had an injury to her
spleen right about here

830
00:31:31.848 --> 00:31:33.724
with some internal bleeding.

831
00:31:33.725 --> 00:31:35.100
Oh. God.

832
00:31:35.101 --> 00:31:36.476
She passed out
from blood loss.

833
00:31:36.477 --> 00:31:38.729
We were able to transfuse her.
and she's now on her way

834
00:31:38.730 --> 00:31:40.939
to surgery
to repair that damage.

835
00:31:40.940 --> 00:31:43.150
This is my fault.

836
00:31:43.151 --> 00:31:44.485
She was trying to--

837
00:31:46.821 --> 00:31:51.283
She booked a trip
for us. for me.

838
00:31:51.284 --> 00:31:54.120
I fought her the whole time.
I've been--

839
00:31:57.248 --> 00:31:59.082
Please don't--

840
00:31:59.083 --> 00:32:02.002
oh. my God.
please don't let her die.

841
00:32:02.003 --> 00:32:03.420
Please.

842
00:32:03.421 --> 00:32:06.132
I can assure you
that she is in excellent hands.

843
00:32:08.217 --> 00:32:09.927
Is this how it works?

844
00:32:09.928 --> 00:32:12.387
How what works?

845
00:32:12.388 --> 00:32:14.932
You think things
are important...

846
00:32:14.933 --> 00:32:18.435
that everything's so important.

847
00:32:18.436 --> 00:32:20.563
And then you end up here
and see.

848
00:32:23.650 --> 00:32:26.985
Yeah. that is how it works.

849
00:32:26.986 --> 00:32:29.905
No. it's a small hole.

850
00:32:29.906 --> 00:32:32.407
Like the size of a dime.
right. Doc?

851
00:32:32.408 --> 00:32:34.868
Mm-hmm.
Yeah. even smaller.

852
00:32:34.869 --> 00:32:36.912
It's a minor enough procedure

853
00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:39.498
that most patients go home
the next day.

854
00:32:39.499 --> 00:32:40.582
And then?

855
00:32:40.583 --> 00:32:42.751
And then they'll know
what it is

856
00:32:42.752 --> 00:32:44.002
and how to treat it.

857
00:32:44.003 --> 00:32:47.090
- Isn't that right?
- Yeah. exactly.

858
00:32:49.092 --> 00:32:52.052
I'm sorry
that they called you.

859
00:32:52.053 --> 00:32:54.054
I never updated the form.
I guess.

860
00:32:54.055 --> 00:32:56.140
No. no. it's okay.
I'm--

861
00:32:57.725 --> 00:33:01.479
You know. they called. and I
was just kind of surprised.

862
00:33:03.648 --> 00:33:05.358
Well. you didn't have
to come.

863
00:33:07.068 --> 00:33:08.277
But I did.

864
00:33:11.823 --> 00:33:14.116
I heard you got married.

865
00:33:14.117 --> 00:33:15.784
Congratulations.

866
00:33:15.785 --> 00:33:17.495
Thank you.

867
00:33:19.455 --> 00:33:22.125
I hope he treats you well.

868
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.004
You deserve to be happy.

869
00:33:31.342 --> 00:33:35.554
I'm really sorry you're going
through this. Michael.

870
00:33:35.555 --> 00:33:37.764
Yeah.

871
00:33:37.765 --> 00:33:40.684
Me too.

872
00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:43.688
But you know me--
I'm a survivor.

873
00:33:48.067 --> 00:33:52.612
Why don't I-I leave you guys
to talk for a few minutes?

874
00:33:52.613 --> 00:33:55.158
I have a patient to check on.

875
00:33:56.576 --> 00:33:58.536
- Sure.
- Yeah.

876
00:34:00.079 --> 00:34:02.539
Mr. Diaz should be improving
after 2 liters.

877
00:34:02.540 --> 00:34:03.957
Blood sugar?

878
00:34:03.958 --> 00:34:05.959
Down from 521 to 436.

879
00:34:05.960 --> 00:34:07.294
That's good. right?

880
00:34:07.295 --> 00:34:08.712
Moving
in the right direction.

881
00:34:08.713 --> 00:34:10.881
Were you able to get ahold
of your mom?

882
00:34:10.882 --> 00:34:13.133
Yes. She's on her way.
She doesn't have a car.

883
00:34:13.134 --> 00:34:15.594
She takes buses.
so it takes longer.

884
00:34:15.595 --> 00:34:18.430
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be.

885
00:34:18.431 --> 00:34:22.017
Current insulin is 0.1 units
per kilo per hour.

886
00:34:22.018 --> 00:34:23.060
Next steps?

887
00:34:23.061 --> 00:34:24.728
Once the glucose
is down to 250.

888
00:34:24.729 --> 00:34:27.397
reduce the insulin to
0.05 units per kilo per hour.

889
00:34:27.398 --> 00:34:29.024
Because you can normalize
the blood sugar

890
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:31.485
before you clear the ketones.
and you don't get hypoglycemia.

891
00:34:31.486 --> 00:34:34.237
But as treatment continues.
you'll have to give IV dextrose

892
00:34:34.238 --> 00:34:36.698
to keep the blood glucose
in between 150 and 200

893
00:34:36.699 --> 00:34:37.991
while the insulin drip
clears the ketones.

894
00:34:37.992 --> 00:34:39.785
Obviously.

895
00:34:39.786 --> 00:34:41.496
I'm sorry. what?

896
00:34:43.247 --> 00:34:44.539
Got it.

897
00:34:44.540 --> 00:34:46.458
Duante. what are you doing
in there. son?

898
00:34:46.459 --> 00:34:47.918
I'm a rabbit.

899
00:34:47.919 --> 00:34:50.212
grabbing all the carrots
before the farmer gets me.

900
00:34:50.213 --> 00:34:51.838
Keep going.

901
00:34:51.839 --> 00:34:55.467
This is a Katz extractor
with a tiny balloon at the end.

902
00:34:55.468 --> 00:34:57.552
What we're gonna do is. we're
gonna slip it past the bead.

903
00:34:57.553 --> 00:34:59.179
inflate the balloon.
try to pull out the bead.

904
00:34:59.180 --> 00:35:01.389
- Is it painful?
- No. he's--he's numbed up.

905
00:35:01.390 --> 00:35:02.933
Made it to level three.

906
00:35:02.934 --> 00:35:04.309
And pretty distracted.

907
00:35:04.310 --> 00:35:06.561
Dad's gonna hold
your head still. okay?

908
00:35:06.562 --> 00:35:09.147
- Look up.
- Okay.

909
00:35:09.148 --> 00:35:13.026
Now go back. perpendicular.

910
00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:15.113
below the turbinates.

911
00:35:16.489 --> 00:35:19.032
You guys ever hear
of John O'Donohue?

912
00:35:19.033 --> 00:35:20.283
- Mm-mm.
- No.

913
00:35:20.284 --> 00:35:21.701
I've been reading him
a lot lately.

914
00:35:21.702 --> 00:35:25.122
He's got this book
of. um. blessings.

915
00:35:25.123 --> 00:35:27.415
And there's this one
about fatherhood.

916
00:35:27.416 --> 00:35:29.127
Really stuck with me.

917
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:32.546
Voilà. One red bead.

918
00:35:32.547 --> 00:35:34.965
Yeah?
How's it go?

919
00:35:34.966 --> 00:35:38.844
The ending goes.
"May you be gentle and loving.

920
00:35:38.845 --> 00:35:40.762
"clear and sure.

921
00:35:40.763 --> 00:35:43.640
"May you trust
in the unseen Providence

922
00:35:43.641 --> 00:35:45.976
"that has chosen you
to be a family.

923
00:35:45.977 --> 00:35:50.063
"May you stand sure
on your ground and know

924
00:35:50.064 --> 00:35:53.358
"that every grace you need
will unfold before you

925
00:35:53.359 --> 00:35:55.861
like all the mornings
of your life."

926
00:35:55.862 --> 00:35:57.946
Hmm. That's good.

927
00:35:57.947 --> 00:36:02.909
I'd add. support your woman
and pack good snacks.

928
00:36:02.910 --> 00:36:04.494
That's beautiful.

929
00:36:04.495 --> 00:36:07.455
And it turns out. there's
no handbook for fatherhood.

930
00:36:07.456 --> 00:36:11.377
So I will take
all the wisdom I can.

931
00:36:12.879 --> 00:36:14.380
Blue bead out.

932
00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:20.844
Anything else?

933
00:36:20.845 --> 00:36:23.471
You tell me.
I have my own report to do.

934
00:36:23.472 --> 00:36:24.556
Anything I left out?

935
00:36:24.557 --> 00:36:25.932
Labs are back on that kid.

936
00:36:25.933 --> 00:36:27.475
We'll follow up
with Mr. Davis.

937
00:36:27.476 --> 00:36:30.313
Yeah. when Mr. Davis
comes off the ceiling.

938
00:36:33.357 --> 00:36:35.483
Jackson Davis...

939
00:36:35.484 --> 00:36:37.819
tox screen negative
for cocaine.

940
00:36:37.820 --> 00:36:42.282
amphetamines. marijuana.
PCP. benzos. and opioids.

941
00:36:42.283 --> 00:36:44.576
- So no drugs in his system?
- Nope.

942
00:36:44.577 --> 00:36:46.870
Taser barbs on the back
of the victim's neck?

943
00:36:46.871 --> 00:36:48.289
Yep.

944
00:36:51.167 --> 00:36:53.293
Changes things. Tony.

945
00:36:53.294 --> 00:36:54.920
Hey. Louie.

946
00:36:54.921 --> 00:36:57.714
- How we doing?
- Not so good.

947
00:36:57.715 --> 00:37:00.050
I could really use a drink.

948
00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:02.719
I f-feel a-a little empty.

949
00:37:02.720 --> 00:37:04.304
Okay. well. empty
is what we want.

950
00:37:04.305 --> 00:37:06.389
And it looks like we are there.

951
00:37:06.390 --> 00:37:09.809
Hey. well. if I can't get
a drink. my tooth.

952
00:37:09.810 --> 00:37:11.311
You--you got to do something.

953
00:37:11.312 --> 00:37:12.520
We're gonna get
right to that.

954
00:37:12.521 --> 00:37:16.274
Let's hang some IV antibiotics.
3 grams of Unasyn.

955
00:37:16.275 --> 00:37:18.318
Excellent.

956
00:37:18.319 --> 00:37:19.569
He's gonna be right back.

957
00:37:19.570 --> 00:37:20.987
We're gonna numb it up
and drain it.

958
00:37:20.988 --> 00:37:22.822
- Ten minutes. tops. okay?
- Oh.

959
00:37:22.823 --> 00:37:25.408
Hey. uh. you said
you met Mr. Zambelli.

960
00:37:25.409 --> 00:37:27.494
the fireworks guy.
on the field.

961
00:37:27.495 --> 00:37:28.536
What field was that?

962
00:37:28.537 --> 00:37:32.207
Uh. n-no more talking.
You got to fix my tooth.

963
00:37:32.208 --> 00:37:33.793
Yeah. deal.

964
00:37:39.966 --> 00:37:42.634
You're Muslim?

965
00:37:42.635 --> 00:37:45.220
I am.

966
00:37:45.221 --> 00:37:46.721
Thank you.

967
00:37:46.722 --> 00:37:48.599
Oh. for what?

968
00:37:49.934 --> 00:37:52.352
After the shooting.
it was the Muslims

969
00:37:52.353 --> 00:37:55.855
that came together for us
in support and...

970
00:37:55.856 --> 00:37:57.649
walked with us.

971
00:37:57.650 --> 00:37:59.276
You raised money.

972
00:37:59.277 --> 00:38:01.027
You...

973
00:38:01.028 --> 00:38:03.905
paid for all the funerals.

974
00:38:03.906 --> 00:38:06.491
Anyway...

975
00:38:06.492 --> 00:38:07.951
thank you.

976
00:38:07.952 --> 00:38:11.079
Hello.
How's it going in here?

977
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.956
Did I miss all the gross stuff?

978
00:38:12.957 --> 00:38:15.000
- Timed it perfectly.
- Excellent.

979
00:38:15.001 --> 00:38:17.335
My job is all about delegation
and time management.

980
00:38:17.336 --> 00:38:19.629
- Oh. not for much longer.
- That is very true.

981
00:38:19.630 --> 00:38:21.214
W-why for not longer?

982
00:38:21.215 --> 00:38:24.217
Because tomorrow I am leaving
to go on sabbatical.

983
00:38:24.218 --> 00:38:27.470
He's leaving us for
three months on a motorcycle.

984
00:38:27.471 --> 00:38:30.056
Motorcycle?
You're joking.

985
00:38:30.057 --> 00:38:32.809
- Why would you do this?
- Why? Why?

986
00:38:32.810 --> 00:38:35.020
- Why? Because--
- You're middle-aged man.

987
00:38:35.021 --> 00:38:36.730
Don't be stupid.

988
00:38:36.731 --> 00:38:38.732
Don't hold back.
Tell me how you really feel.

989
00:38:38.733 --> 00:38:41.318
Forgive me for being blunt.
Dr. Robinavitch.

990
00:38:41.319 --> 00:38:43.945
but how old are you. huh--50?

991
00:38:43.946 --> 00:38:45.989
- Ish.
- Ish.

992
00:38:45.990 --> 00:38:49.993
50-ish-year-old man
on a motorcycle--

993
00:38:49.994 --> 00:38:50.911
very sad.

994
00:39:02.131 --> 00:39:03.841
I. um...

995
00:39:05.676 --> 00:39:07.969
I-I-I don't know what to say.

996
00:39:07.970 --> 00:39:10.263
Have you ever heard of ITP?

997
00:39:10.264 --> 00:39:11.265
I never did.

998
00:39:13.434 --> 00:39:15.685
I really appreciate you
bringing her here. okay?

999
00:39:15.686 --> 00:39:17.979
Of course.
What do you think I am?

1000
00:39:17.980 --> 00:39:19.314
Oh. that's right.

1001
00:39:19.315 --> 00:39:20.940
You think I'm some kind
of child abuser.

1002
00:39:20.941 --> 00:39:22.609
- No. I never said that--
- The fuck you didn't.

1003
00:39:22.610 --> 00:39:24.694
In front of all those people.
you made it sound like

1004
00:39:24.695 --> 00:39:25.862
she might have
been getting hurt

1005
00:39:25.863 --> 00:39:28.114
while I was watching her.
like it was my fault.

1006
00:39:28.115 --> 00:39:29.407
You basically said
the same thing about me.

1007
00:39:29.408 --> 00:39:31.076
No. I said that
you guys roughhouse--

1008
00:39:31.077 --> 00:39:32.702
that's all--because you do.

1009
00:39:32.703 --> 00:39:34.913
You know I would never hurt
my daughter.

1010
00:39:34.914 --> 00:39:36.998
Actually. I don't.

1011
00:39:36.999 --> 00:39:39.918
I've known you six months.
You could be anybody.

1012
00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:42.003
Okay. well. I am sorry
for what I said. okay?

1013
00:39:42.004 --> 00:39:43.713
I was upset.
and I-I was worried.

1014
00:39:43.714 --> 00:39:45.256
And I just--
I said something stupid.

1015
00:39:45.257 --> 00:39:46.591
- And I just--
- You think?

1016
